Review.Titre: I ordered a specific part for my furnace to convert from Fuel Oil/kerosene to propane
Review.Contenu: I ordered a specific part for my furnace, I chose to go thru the company that we purchased the furnace through 5 years ago. With the cost of fuel oil going up this was necessary to be able to afford to heat our me. I purchased a burner assembly which will convert my furnace from fuel oil kerosene to propane. I scheduled the technician to come in and install it and unfortunately I was not sent the correct parts to be able to do so. This is the first time that I've ordered any parts from this company, I'm not upset as far as a product being missed pulled in the ship it happens.. my frustration lies with me immediately reaching out sending an email of the issue and concerns and have yet been contacted by a customer service rep. I was very clear of the situation and what situation that I am in right now to be able to heat my home. I feel, because of the lack of response the customer service is not this company's number one priority. Honestly I'm not certain if I would order through this company again, I guess when I reach out to inquire the status and see what kind of verbal communication I received will determine that.

Review.Titre: Arrived Damaged due to poor packaging by manufacturer, IMHO.
Review.Contenu: I assume Partshnc is just a distributor and had little control over this outcome.  Ordering was easy and delivery took 5 days, prompt enough, no complaint.  My issue was the part arrived in a mildly damaged condition.  I blame a lack of careful packaging with no thought to immobilizing the part.  It was thrown loose into a box with the two gaskets, and left to freely bounce around; even though the fins cause it to be a little fragile.  I assume it is still functional, but it has more damaged, crushed & mangled fins than is justifiable when I paid a "New" part price.  I expect it in "New" part condition.  The only reason I didn't contact and discuss a replacement is I had the same issue with the Primary heat exchanger for this furnace from another vendor, and other potential suppliers were all out of stock.  Under current supply constraints, I am willing to try to comb out the fins myself and use it, but I shouldn't have too.
